# Cline Rules — EdenCORP Standards

## Required before coding

1. Check for EdenCORP standards repository locally:
   - `./standards`
   - `../standards`
   - `./.eden/standards`
2. If unavailable, clone automatically when tools allow:
   - `git clone https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards`
3. If cloning is unavailable in this environment, request user action:
   - "Please clone `https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards` so I can read the standards before implementation."
4. Read all standards docs (all root-level Markdown standards files and relevant templates), not a subset.
5. Extract and persist requirements to project memory.
   - Preferred: native persistent memory
   - Fallback: `.eden/agent-memory/standards-memory.md`
6. Load stored memory before any future implementation task.

## Behavior

- Apply standards as first-class constraints for code and reviews.
- Keep work scoped and avoid unrelated changes.
- Follow required testing and security practices from standards docs.
- Ask for clarification whenever standards and user goals conflict.
